Columns.Name: ShipmentId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Shipment.

Columns.Name: PeriodStartTimestamp
Columns.Description: The period start timestamp that the shipment was at the shipping location.

Columns.Name: PeriodEndTimestamp
Columns.Description: The period end timestamp that the shipment was at the shipping location.

Columns.Name: VendorId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Vendor.

Columns.Name: RfidTagId
Columns.Description:
The unique identifier of a RFID Tag.

The transmitter/receiver pair or transceiver plus the information storage mechanism attached to the object is referred to as the tag, transponder, electronic label, code plate and various other terms. 

Although transponder is technically the most accurate, the most common term and the one preferred by the Automatic Identification Manufacturers is tag.

Columns.Name: ShipmentLocationGpsLongitudePosition
Columns.Description:
The GPS position of the Shipment expressed in longitude. This may be an in-transit location.

Ex:
GPS Coords (Ex= 39deg 58.589min) - seconds are converted to decimal format.

Columns.Name: ShipmentLocationGpsLatitudePosition
Columns.Description:
The GPS position of the Shipment Location. expressed in latitude. This may be an in-transit location.

Ex:
GPS Coords (Ex= 39deg 58.589min) - seconds are converted to decimal format.

Columns.Name: ShippingLocationId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Shipping Location.

Columns.Name: LocationId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Location.

Columns.Name: PlannedShipmentLocationTurnaroundTime
Columns.Description: The planned amount of turnaround time to transit the shipment to the next shipment location of the route.

Columns.Name: ActualShipmentLocationTurnaroundTime
Columns.Description: The amount of turnaround time to transit the shipment to the next shipment location of the route.

Columns.Name: InformationAcquisitionMethodId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of an Information Acquisition Method.

Columns.Name: ShipmentLegNumber
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of the Shipment Leg Number, which equals the shipment leg 'sequence number'.

Columns.Name: ApplicationCommunicationId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of an Application Communication.
